## 2. Kit Showcase Plan

### 2.1 Foundations page — new Section V "Pi-* Utilities"

**File:** `frontend/src/app/pages/foundations/foundations.page.ts`

**Current sections (per basher):** I (Палитра), II (Типографика), III (Spacing & Radius), IV (Grid).

**New section (V):** "Pi-* Utilities" — showcases the 3 TZ-93 utilities in isolation (like the existing palette/typography swatches).

**Content:**

```html
<app-pi-section title="Pi-* Utilities" hint="TZ-93/95 · 3 architectural primitives" eyebrow="V">
  <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground max-w-prose mb-stack-lg">
    Architectural primitives adopted from
    <code class="font-mono text-[11px]">stitch_professional_desktop_crm_refinement</code>.
    See <code class="font-mono text-[11px]">tasks/TZ-93.md</code> for the full adoption matrix
    (what was adopted, adapted, rejected).
  </p>

  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-gutter">
    <!-- .pi-tech-label demo -->
    <div class="pi-corner-marks hairline bg-paper p-stack-lg relative">
      <span class="pi-tech-label absolute top-2 right-2">REF: PIT.01</span>
      <h3 class="font-title-sm text-ink mb-stack-sm">pi-tech-label</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
        10px monospace tech label, uppercase, 0.1em letter-spacing,
        AAA contrast via <code class="font-mono text-[11px]">--color-muted-foreground-strong</code>.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- .pi-corner-marks demo -->
    <div class="pi-corner-marks hairline bg-paper p-stack-lg">
      <h3 class="font-title-sm text-ink mb-stack-sm">pi-corner-marks</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
        8px L-shaped corner marks via <code class="font-mono text-[11px]">::before/::after</code>
        pseudo-elements. Pure CSS, no DOM pollution.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- .pi-dashed-panel demo -->
    <div class="pi-dashed-panel p-stack-lg bg-paper">
      <h3 class="font-title-sm text-ink mb-stack-sm">pi-dashed-panel</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
        1px dashed border for empty states and draft-style surfaces.
        Lower perceptual contrast — apply only on near-empty surfaces.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</app-pi-section>
```

**Acceptance:**
- Section V renders below existing Section IV (Grid).
- 3 demo cards each show one utility in isolation.
- Cards use Paper & Ink conventions (`hairline`, `bg-paper`, `text-ink`, `text-muted-foreground`).

