## 4. Implementation Plan (Layer 1 trivial)

5 atomic commits, ordered least-risky first:

| # | Commit | Scope | Risk |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | `docs: [TZ-95] add Pi-* Utilities section to paper-and-ink.md` | `docs/paper-and-ink.md` | Low (additive doc) |
| 2 | `docs: [TZ-95] add Border & Utility Conventions to add-new-page.md` | `docs/add-new-page.md` | Low (additive doc) |
| 3 | `feat(kit): [TZ-95] add Section V Pi-* Utilities to foundations.page` | `foundations.page.ts` | Low (additive section) |
| 4 | `feat(kit): [TZ-95] augment forms + overlays with architectural demos` | `forms.page.ts` + `overlays.page.ts` | Low (additive demos) |
| 5 | `feat(kit): [TZ-95] add 4th card (table context) to playground Section III` | `theme-editor.page.ts` (optional) | Low (additive card) |

**Rationale:**
- Commits 1-2 are doc-only (lowest risk).
- Commit 3 adds a new section to the most-trafficked kit page (foundations).
- Commit 4 augments 2 existing kit pages with small demos.
- Commit 5 is optional — depends on whether the 4th card (table context) adds value.

---

## 5. Risks and Tradeoffs

| Риск | Вероятность | Митигация |
|---|---|---|
| Browser-use visual verify BLOCKED by authGuard on /kit/* | High (guaranteed) | Typecheck + manual code review is the primary verification gate. Document in commit body. Consider folding TZ-93.1 (auth wall resolution) into this TZ if user wants end-to-end visual verify. |
| Doc sections grow too long, dilute the "why" narrative | Low | Keep new sections concise (table + lists, not prose). Cross-reference TZ-93/94/95 specs for full rationale. |
| Kit page demos use `pi-*` utilities but adopters don't know when to use them | Medium | The new `add-new-page.md` convention section + paper-and-ink.md section explicitly documents the decision tree. |
| 4th card in playground (table context) overlaps with foundations Section V | Low | Section V is a static reference; Section III playground is interactive. Different purposes. |
| Existing kit sections get refactored by mistake | Low | Strict additive scope. No existing sections removed/restructured. |
| `pi-corner-marks` 8px looks wrong on small form field demos | Low | Form field demos use `p-stack-lg` (24px padding) — plenty of room for 8px L-shapes. |

---

## 6. Definition of Done

- 5 atomic commits in `main` (or 4 if the optional 4th card is skipped).
- `docs/paper-and-ink.md` has the new "Pi-* Architectural Utilities" section.
- `docs/add-new-page.md` has the new "Border & Utility Conventions" section.
- 4 kit pages (foundations, forms, overlays, playground) each have 1 new section/demo demonstrating the architectural patterns.
- Frontend typecheck: 0 errors (`pnpm exec tsc -p tsconfig.app.json --noEmit`).
- No new `box-shadow`, `rounded-md/lg/3xl`, `bg-white` introduced.
- All hairline borders use `var(--color-rule)` (warm, not pure black).
- Cross-references between docs ↔ kit sections work (links resolve).
- `verify-status.sh` FAIL count unchanged.
- Browser-use visual verify: **deferred** (authGuard blocks /kit/* — see TZ-93 known limitation).

